President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to give feedback on the Public Investment Corporation inquiry. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to give feedback on the Public Investment Corporation inquiry. The commission spent a year holding public hearings and receiving submissions. READ: Matjila laments PIC exit The President's spokesperson, Khusela Diko, says he will release the findings and recommendations as soon as the process is completed. “The president has recently met the Judge Lex Mpati, who was chairing that PIC commission. They have taken him through the report. "He's engaged the Minister of Finance on the report and they are looking at the recommendations with the intent to put together a roadmap,” Diko said.